{
  "page": "Dragonseed",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragonseeds.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/c/cb/Dragonseeds.png/350px-Dragonseeds.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/cb/Dragonseeds.png/525px-Dragonseeds.png 1.5x, /images/c/cb/Dragonseeds.png 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragonseeds.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Dragonseeds, as depicted in the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Game_of_Thrones\" title=\"Game of Thrones\">Game of Thrones</a></i> featurette, <i>The Dance of Dragons</i></div></div></div>\n<p><b>Dragonseeds</b> is a term to describe the <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastards</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyrians\" title=\"Valyrians\">Valyrian</a> descent who are fathered in the islands in the <a href=\"/index.php/Blackwater_Bay\" title=\"Blackwater Bay\">Blackwater Bay</a>, including <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone_(island)\" title=\"Dragonstone (island)\">Dragonstone</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a>. They are sometimes also called <b>\"seeds\"</b> for short.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Origins\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Origins</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#The_Dance_of_the_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The Dance of the Dragons</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Named_Dragonseeds\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Named Dragonseeds</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Origins\">Origins</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Origins\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/index.php/Custom\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Custom\">custom</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/First_night\" title=\"First night\">first night</a> — that when <a href=\"/index.php/Smallfolk\" title=\"Smallfolk\">smallfolk</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Marriage\" title=\"Marriage\">marry</a>, their lord or king has the privilege to bed the bride on the wedding night — had been greatly resented in the <a href=\"/index.php/Seven_Kingdoms\" title=\"Seven Kingdoms\">Seven Kingdoms</a>. However, it was less protested on <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a>, where the Targaryens had ruled for centuries, because there the common folk viewed their beautiful, foreign rulers almost as <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> When a <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_of_Dragonstone\" title=\"Lord of Dragonstone\">Lord of Dragonstone</a> took his rights according to the first night custom, the bride considered herself \"blessed\" if she conceived a child.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> A child born of the union was greatly valued, and the lord would grant the mother generous gifts of <a href=\"/index.php/Gold\" title=\"Gold\">gold</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Silk\" title=\"Silk\">silk</a> and land. The bastards were said to be \"born of dragonseed\", and in time, became known as \"dragonseeds\" or \"seeds\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The term \"dragonseed\" existed for some generations before the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, as King <a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a> noted in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_58_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">58&#160;AC</a> that Targaryen bastards fathered during the first night were often called this. Jaehaerys admitted that it was considered something of an open secret that his grandfather <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon's</a> great friend and commander <a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a> was in truth Aegon's bastard half-brother, though he knew nothing about Orys's mother or the circumstances of his birth (such as whether he was conceived through the first night or just a youthful dalliance by <a href=\"/index.php/Aerion_Targaryen_(son_of_Daemion)\" title=\"Aerion Targaryen (son of Daemion)\">Aegon's father</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Though the right of the first night ended when it was outlawed by King Jaehaerys, some Targaryens continued to carry on relationships with the daughters of innkeeps and the wives of fishermen. Seeds and the sons of seeds thus remained plentiful on Dragonstone and surrounding areas, and there were many on Dragonstone who could rightly claim — or at least suspect — that some Targaryen blood ran in their veins.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_Dance_of_the_Dragons\">The Dance of the Dragons</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: The Dance of the Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:352px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg/350px-Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7b/Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg/525px-Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7b/Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg/700px-Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Dragonseeds_by_enife.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Dragonseeds of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>: <a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam Velaryon</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf White</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh Hammer</a>, by Enife ©</div></div></div>\n<p>During the civil war known as the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, Prince <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a> realized that his mother Queen <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a>'s faction, <a href=\"/index.php/The_blacks\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"The blacks\">the blacks</a>, had many <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragons</a> but was in need of <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonriders</a>. In <a href=\"/index.php/129_AC\" title=\"129 AC\">129&#160;AC</a>, he offered lands, riches, and <a href=\"/index.php/Knighthood\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knighthood\">knighthood</a> to any man that could master a dragon; his sons would be ennobled, his daughters wed to lords.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> According to <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Testimony_of_Mushroom\" title=\"The Testimony of Mushroom\">The Testimony of Mushroom</a></i>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">eponymous</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Fool\" title=\"Fool\">fool</a> had prompted Jacaerys to make this search.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Jacaerys's offer gained the attention of more than just dragonseeds. Most candidates failed and were either killed or burned by the dragons. (These included Rhaenyra's <a href=\"/index.php/Lord_Commander_of_the_Kingsguard\" title=\"Lord Commander of the Kingsguard\">Lord Commander</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Queensguard\" title=\"Queensguard\">Queensguard</a>, Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Steffon_Darklyn\" title=\"Steffon Darklyn\">Steffon Darklyn</a>, and also Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Gormon_Massey\" title=\"Gormon Massey\">Gormon Massey</a>.) Grand Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Munkun\" title=\"Munkun\">Munkun</a> dubbed this event \"the <a href=\"/index.php/Sowing_of_the_Seeds\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Sowing of the Seeds\">Sowing of the Seeds</a>\", whilst others called it \"the Red Sowing\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Nevertheless, in the end <a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh Hammer</a> bonded with the dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf White</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Silverwing\" title=\"Silverwing\">Silverwing</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_of_Hull\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Addam of Hull\">Addam of Hull</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a> with <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a>. It is unconfirmed if the successful candidates truly had Targaryen blood, or if they did, if that ancestry is what allowed them to master the dragons. But whatever their origin in truth, the successful baseborn dragonriders were called dragonseeds for the remainder of the war and within historical records.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>Jacaerys prepared to lead the four new dragonriders in an attack on <a href=\"/index.php/King%27s_Landing\" title=\"King&#39;s Landing\">King's Landing</a> the first full <a href=\"/index.php/Moon\" title=\"Moon\">moon</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a>, but before that could happen, news reached <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonstone\" title=\"Dragonstone\">Dragonstone</a> of the attack by the <a href=\"/index.php/Triarchy\" title=\"Triarchy\">Triarchy</a> on the <i><a href=\"/index.php/Gay_Abandon\" title=\"Gay Abandon\">Gay Abandon</a></i>, which had been escorting Jacaerys's half-brothers <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_III_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon III Targaryen\">Aegon</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Viserys_II_Targaryen\" title=\"Viserys II Targaryen\">Viserys Targaryen</a>. Instead, Jacaerys and his fellow dragonriders flew against the Triachy's fleet and fought them in the <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_the_Gullet\" title=\"Battle of the Gullet\">Battle of the Gullet</a>. Jacaerys and his dragon <a href=\"/index.php/Vermax\" title=\"Vermax\">Vermax</a> died during the battle.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtpatq.7B.7B.7B2.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/index.php/130_AC\" title=\"130 AC\">130&#160;AC</a>, after the <a href=\"/index.php/Two_Betrayers\" title=\"Two Betrayers\">betrayal</a> of Hugh Hammer and Ulf White at the <a href=\"/index.php/First_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"First Battle of Tumbleton\">First Battle of Tumbleton</a>, Queen Rhaenyra and most of her council believed none of the other dragonseeds could be trusted, and ordered their arrest.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Addam Velaryon escaped upon his dragon Seasmoke, but later proved his loyalty at the <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Battle_of_Tumbleton\" title=\"Second Battle of Tumbleton\">Second Battle of Tumbleton</a>, in which he perished.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup> In the case of Nettles, it was not only arrest that was ordered, but also execution, because she had allegedly become the lover of Rhaenyra's husband <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>; however, the girl fled upon Sheepstealer and was never seen again \"at court or castle\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rtwoiafthe_targaryen_kings:_aegon_ii.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Named_Dragonseeds\">Named Dragonseeds</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Named Dragonseeds\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aegon_Orys_(Invasion).jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg/300px-Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"195\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/e/e2/Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg/450px-Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/e/e2/Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg/600px-Aegon_Orys_%28Invasion%29.jpg 2x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/index.php/File:Aegon_Orys_(Invasion).jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a>, his alleged dragonseed half-brother © HBO from <i>Game of Thrones: Conquest &amp; Rebellion</i></div></div></div>\n<p><a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a> was called a dragonseed, since even the Targaryens themselves believed he was the half-brother of <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">Aegon I Targaryen</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>During the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>:\n</p>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/index.php/Hugh_Hammer\" title=\"Hugh Hammer\">Hugh Hammer</a>, a blacksmith's bastard, bonded with <a href=\"/index.php/Vermithor\" title=\"Vermithor\">Vermithor</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Ulf_White\" title=\"Ulf White\">Ulf White</a>, a <a href=\"/index.php/Man-at-arms\" title=\"Man-at-arms\">man-at-arms</a>, bonded with <a href=\"/index.php/Silverwing\" title=\"Silverwing\">Silverwing</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam of Hull</a>, bonded with <a href=\"/index.php/Seasmoke\" title=\"Seasmoke\">Seasmoke</a>. Was <a href=\"/index.php/Bastardy#Legitimization\" title=\"Bastardy\">legitimized</a> as Addam Velaryon and made heir to <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a> shortly thereafter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn of Hull</a>, the younger brother of Addam of Hull. Unable to find <a href=\"/index.php/Grey_Ghost\" title=\"Grey Ghost\">Grey Ghost</a>, rejected by <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a>, but legitimized as Alyn Velaryon nevertheless.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a>, bonded with <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a> by feeding it sheep each morning.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/index.php/Silver_Denys\" title=\"Silver Denys\">Silver Denys</a>, claimed to have been descended from a bastard son of King <a href=\"/index.php/Maegor_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Maegor I Targaryen\">Maegor I Targaryen</a>. Had an arm torn off by Sheepstealer, and was devoured with his sons by the <a href=\"/index.php/Cannibal_(dragon)\" title=\"Cannibal (dragon)\">Cannibal</a> while trying to staunch his wound.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Dragonseeds, they call them. It is not a thing to boast of, but it has happened, mayhaps more often than we would care to admit. Such children are cherished, though.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>, to his wife <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><a href=\"/index.php/Orys_Baratheon\" title=\"Orys Baratheon\">Orys Baratheon</a> himself was a dragonseed, a <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> brother to <a href=\"/index.php/Aegon_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Aegon I Targaryen\">our grandsire</a>. Whether he was conceived of a <a href=\"/index.php/First_night\" title=\"First night\">first night</a> I cannot say, but Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Aerion_Targaryen_(son_of_Daemion)\" title=\"Aerion Targaryen (son of Daemion)\">Aerion</a> was his father, that was well-known.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabjaehaerys_and_alysanne_-_their_triumphs_and_tragedies.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Jaehaerys_I_Targaryen\" title=\"Jaehaerys I Targaryen\">Jaehaerys I Targaryen</a>, to his wife <a href=\"/index.php/Alysanne_Targaryen\" title=\"Alysanne Targaryen\">Alysanne</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Under the sheets and in the woodpiles, wherever you <a href=\"/index.php/Targaryen\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Targaryen\">Targaryens</a> spilled your <a href=\"/index.php/Silver\" title=\"Silver\">silver</a> seed.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>, to <a href=\"/index.php/Jacaerys_Velaryon\" title=\"Jacaerys Velaryon\">Jacaerys Velaryon</a>, when asked where to find more <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">dragonriders</a>, per <i><a href=\"/index.php/The_Testimony_of_Mushroom\" title=\"The Testimony of Mushroom\">The Testimony of Mushroom</a></i></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>That <a href=\"/index.php/Addam_Velaryon\" title=\"Addam Velaryon\">Addam</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Alyn_Velaryon\" title=\"Alyn Velaryon\">Alyn</a> were dragonseed no man who looked upon them could doubt.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;writings of <a href=\"/index.php/Gyldayn\" title=\"Gyldayn\">Gyldayn</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Dragonseed&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.00</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.01</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.02</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.03</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_the_red_dragon_and_the_gold.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.04</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dyin